%% ShopFlow — Order Intake Sequence / Data-Flow Diagram
%% Fills the gap where README references docs/diagrams/shopflow-architecture.png (missing).
%% Drop into projects/project-1-shopflow/docs/diagrams/
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant P as Partner / Web / Mobile
    participant FD as Front Door (WAF)
    participant AP as APIM (Std v2)
    participant OA as Orders Function (EP1)
    participant SB as Service Bus (orders-inbound)
    participant FP as Fulfillment Processor
    participant SQL as Azure SQL (ZR + failover group)
    participant TE as SB Topic (order-events)
    participant LA as Logic Apps (Std)

    P->>FD: HTTPS POST /orders (JWT)
    FD->>AP: Forward (edge cache miss)
    AP->>AP: Validate JWT, rate-limit, inject correlation-id
    AP->>OA: POST /orders
    OA->>OA: Validate payload
    OA->>SB: Enqueue order message
    OA-->>P: 202 Accepted + status URL
    Note over OA,SB: Load leveling — intake survives fulfillment outage
    SB->>FP: Trigger (competing consumer)
    FP->>SQL: Persist order (idempotent upsert)
    FP->>TE: Publish order-event
    TE->>LA: Fan-out (partner webhook sub)
    TE->>LA: Fan-out (email notify sub)
    TE->>SQL: Audit sub (immutable trail)
    Note over SB,FP: Poison messages route to DLQ + alert on DLQ depth
